text.paragraph:
Priapism has been reported during postmarketing surveillance [see 

                              Adverse Reactions (6.8)

                           ]. Severe priapism may require surgical intervention.

Increased plasma concentrations of risperidone and 9-hydroxyrisperidone occur in patients with severe renal impairment (creatinine clearance <30 mL/min/1.73 m2), and an increase in the free fraction of risperidone is seen in patients with severe hepatic impairment. A lower starting dose should be used in such patients [see 

                              Dosage and Administration (2.4)

                           ].

